<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,303,500,526]" box="[189,303,500,526]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,500,526]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,500,526]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[188,1399,554,709]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Prior to this study, the genus comprised four species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stonedahl, 1988" authorityName="Stonedahl" authorityYear="1988" box="[809,1115,554,580]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Mertila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabah">
<emphasis box="[809,918,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. sabah</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stonedahl G. M." box="[925,1115,554,580]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref23015" refString="Stonedahl G. M. 1988. Revisions of Dioclerus, Harpedona, Mertila, Myiocapsus, Prodromus and Thaumastomiris (Heteroptera: Miridae, Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 187: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1988">Stonedahl, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stonedahl, 1988" authorityName="Stonedahl" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Mertila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarawak">
<emphasis box="[1129,1267,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. sarawak</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stonedahl G. M." pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref23015" refString="Stonedahl G. M. 1988. Revisions of Dioclerus, Harpedona, Mertila, Myiocapsus, Prodromus and Thaumastomiris (Heteroptera: Miridae, Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 187: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1988">Stonedahl, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[263,377,597,624]" name="Malaysia" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1904" box="[397,566,597,623]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Mertila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malayensis">
<emphasis box="[397,566,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. malayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[582,694,597,623]" name="Malaysia" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[706,841,597,623]" name="Philippines" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[852,971,597,624]" name="Indonesia" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stonedahl" authorityYear="1988" box="[1041,1160,597,623]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Mertila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bhamo">
<emphasis box="[1041,1160,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. bhamo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1175,1261,597,623]" name="Myanmar" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Burma</collectingCountry>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Stonedahl G. M." pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref23015" refString="Stonedahl G. M. 1988. Revisions of Dioclerus, Harpedona, Mertila, Myiocapsus, Prodromus and Thaumastomiris (Heteroptera: Miridae, Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 187: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1988">Stonedahl (1988)</bibRefCitation>
also recorded the last species from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[687,747,639,665]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
based on a single female without locality data from the 
<collectingCountry box="[189,226,682,708]" name="United States of America" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">US</collectingCountry>
port interception material. Description of one new 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1904" box="[828,916,682,708]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Mertila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,916,682,708]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Mertila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[1080,1140,682,708]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
is given below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,1399,747,859]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1904" box="[319,407,747,773]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Mertila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[319,407,747,773]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Mertila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be recognized among other eccritotarsines by the bicolored, bright reddish and bluish black dorsum, shape of transverse head, structure of the anterior part of the pronotum and the male genitalia. Refer to discussion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1911" box="[633,754,833,859]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Lopidolon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[633,754,833,859]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Lopidolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for details.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,725,897,924]" box="[189,725,897,924]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,725,897,924]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,725,897,924]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Key to species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1904" box="[530,620,897,924]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Mertila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[530,620,897,924]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Mertila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[658,725,898,924]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
