<keyLead pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
1. Head dark reddish; pronotum, scutellum and hemelytron uniformly black (
<figureCitation box="[1164,1299,952,978]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="44.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[233,1383,291,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-17@44.[189,1398,274,1854]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus of Mertila Distant, 1904 and Namyatovia gen. nov. spp. A–C. Mertila rubrocephala sp. nov., ♂, UASB. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and pronotum in dorsal view. C. Abdomen in ventral view. D–F. Namyatovia castlerockensis gen. et sp. nov., ♂, UASB. D. Dorsal view. E. Head and pronotum. F. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690368/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 3A–B</figureCitation>
