<figureCitation box="[503,600,1123,1149]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="49.[189,232,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[277,1345,291,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-12@49.[189,1398,265,1811]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="Fig. 8. Dorsal view, male genitalia and label data of type specimens for Mertila spp. A–C. Mertila bhamo Stonedahl, 1988, holotype, AMNH_PBI 00342529, NHM. D–E. Mertila malayensis Distant, 1904, ♂, lectotype, NHMUK010096278, NHM. F. Mertila malayensis Distant, 1904, paralectotype, AMNH_PBI 00342600, NHM. G. Mertila sarawak Stonedahl,1988, holotype, ♂, NHMUK010096279, NHM. H. Mertila sarawak Stonedahl, 1988, paratype, AMNH_PBI 00342601, NHM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690380/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Tibiae and antennal segment II dark brown. Male genitalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[234,323,1165,1192]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="49.[189,232,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[277,1345,291,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-12@49.[189,1398,265,1811]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="Fig. 8. Dorsal view, male genitalia and label data of type specimens for Mertila spp. A–C. Mertila bhamo Stonedahl, 1988, holotype, AMNH_PBI 00342529, NHM. D–E. Mertila malayensis Distant, 1904, ♂, lectotype, NHMUK010096278, NHM. F. Mertila malayensis Distant, 1904, paralectotype, AMNH_PBI 00342600, NHM. G. Mertila sarawak Stonedahl,1988, holotype, ♂, NHMUK010096279, NHM. H. Mertila sarawak Stonedahl, 1988, paratype, AMNH_PBI 00342601, NHM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690380/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
..................................................................................................... 
